an algorithm for the probability ofthe union of a large number of events.wan algorithm is presented which efficiently evaluatesthe probability for the union of n independent and not mutually exclusive events. the problem is thatof evaluating the sums of the products of all possible combinations of n variables in minimum time and storage space.cacm september, miller, g. d..kalgorithm, probability, optimum, storage vs. timecompromise, set union, mutually exclusive events.c. . .ca jb february ,   : am